data.title: Classic Rock 96.1
data.meta_description: I grew up on the east coast, but have lived in Texas for over 20 years -  two different times in Dallas-Fort Worth, a long stretch in Austin, & now here in Tyler-Longview.  I...
data.text:
Cool Off With Free Epic Waters Passes

Spend the day with your family escaping the Texas summer heat. Win a 4-pack of water park tickets!

Win Tickets to Foreigner & Whitesnake Concert In Dallas July 21!

Register now for free tickets, & you could be inside Irving's Toyota Music Factory for the show on us!

See REO & Chicago In Dallas, On Us!

Win free tickets to the show & be at Dos Equis Pavilion on June 29th, when Kevin Cronin leads REO Speedwagon onto the concert stage. You'll see Rock & Roll Hall Of Fame band Chicago that night too!

Last Chance To Win Tickets For Next Saturday’s Cheap Trick & Poison Concert

Don't miss your shot at comped seats for their show in the Dallas Metroplex!

Win A Fun Night Out With Marshall Tucker

Celebrate Memorial Weekend at Choctaw Casino in Grant, Oklahoma, with free tickets to Saturday night's Marshall Tucker Band concert. Register now!

Fleetwood Mac’s Comin’ To Dallas- See ‘Em On Us!

The concert's next February 7th at the AAC, & we've got free tickets. Sign-up to win your pair now!

Win Free Tickets To See Steely Dan & The Doobies

Donald Fagen's new Steely Dan lineup will share the stage with the Doobie Brothers on May 25th in Irving. You can be there on us!

One Final Congratulations For Our 2018 Bracket Challenge Players

Tyler-Longview's Top 3 winners of Classic Rock 96-1 & Walk-On's 2018 Bracket Challenge are officially revealed!

2nd Straight Bonus Week: 96-Minute Music-Marathons All Day Long While You Work

For the 2nd strait Monday through Friday, we start @ 9am, & when one ends, another begins, all the way til 7. Over 9 hours of commercial-free classic rock while you work.

Special Bonus This Week: 96-Minute Music-Marathons All Day Long While You Work

This Monday through Friday we'll start 'em at 9am as usual, but as soon as one ends, another begins, all the way 'til just past 6:30pm. That's over 9 strait hours of commercial-free classic rock marathons to make your time on the job a little bit better.

Big Week For Concerts: America, Ringo, Loggins, CDB Will All Be Here Plus More to Come!

Four events are set for the 1st five nights of the month. America kicks it off in Tyler Thursday, while Charlie Daniels wraps up the series Sunday in Longview. Plus, new shows have been added to our calendar. Check 'em out!
